(455, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/03/12/isaac-keyet-wordpress-is-mobile/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Isaac Keyet: WordPress is Mobile</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://buddypress.org/2013/03/buddypress-1-7-beta-2/'' title=''Tuesday’s getting even more terrific as we announce the second beta of BuddyPress 1.7! Building on a solid first beta, beta 2 has a number of bug fixes and improvements, mainly around the theme compatibility and admin screens. For those of you interested in a changelog between beta 1 and 2, check out this report in Trac. Now’s the time to test your themes an [&hellip;]''>BuddyPress: BuddyPress 1.7 Beta 2</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://josephscott.org/archives/2013/03/i-am-speaking-at-the-openwest-conference/'' title=''The OpenWest Conference is happening May 2-4, 2013 (formerly the Utah Open Source Conference) at Utah Valley University in Orem, Utah. This year the keynote speakers are Rasmus Lerdorf, creator of PHP, and Mark Callaghan, lead of the MySQL engineering team at Facebook. For my part I’ll be giving three different presentations this time around. First up is “Si [&hellip;]''>Joseph: I am Speaking at the OpenWest Conference</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/x7WcwEeaJQk/'' title=''There has been a lot of talk lately about working from home and maintaining a distributed workforce. Web-based software, like WordPress, Joomla, and Drupal, are taking over the publishing industry and allow you to work from anywhere with an internet connection. Though, even though they can be managed  from home, working from home and maintaining a distribute [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: Do You Work From Home?</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/03/12/essential-seo-link-building-101/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Martin Reed: Essential SEO + Link Building 101</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
