(239, 2, '2013-03-11 06:47:35', '2013-03-11 06:47:35', '<div>Hi, my name is Anne Tang. I am 9 years old. I have big brown eyes and really dark brown hair and tan skin. I enjoy reading, writing, and drawing. I am known for my art and great stories. I really like the color blue. It is a soothing color and is the color of water and the sky. I go to school at Bethel Springs Elementary School. I am in fourth grade and is in Mrs. Eileen Ferguson’s class. I have a lot of friends  <wbr />there: Madison Wesley, Judith (Judy) Yocum, Mikayla Anderson, Victoria Snyder, Sophia Sands, Celia Tran, and a lot more people! <wbr /> I like the series, Warrior Cats by Erin Hunter. I’m in the orchestra. I play the violin. I like it a lot. Even though it is challenging, it is a fun and great instrument. I often have to be careful in the cafeteria. I am vegan which means that I can’t eat or drink stuff that have milk, eggs, meat, or honey in them. I live in Pennsylvania USA. Feel free to email me; my email:<a href="https://profiles.google.com/?hl=en&amp;tab=mX">tangxinyuan909@gmail.com</a>.</div>\r\n<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">My other Chinese name is Xinyuan（唐心缘）. But Anne is easier. My favorite sports are tennis, volleyball, soccer, and basketball. My favorite place to go on  <wbr />vacation is Ocean City. I like it’s beach and shops. I like to eat pizza and drink soda. I <wbr /> always look forward to Christmas. You have winter break and you barely learn at school! Then when you get home, you disappear into a pile of gifts! When it is spring break, I go to China. Then stray cats cuddle in my lap. I love the comfort I get from the stroking and purring.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">That is a bit about me!</span>', '[Anne-连载2]心缘在美国成长', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anne-%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd2%e5%bf%83%e7%bc%98%e5%9c%a8%e7%be%8e%e5%9b%bd%e6%88%90%e9%95%bf', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:47:35', '2013-03-11 06:47:35', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=239', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(240, 2, '2013-03-11 06:47:30', '2013-03-11 06:47:30', '<div>Hi, my name is Anne Tang. I am 9 years old. I have big brown eyes and really dark brown hair and tan skin. I enjoy reading, writing, and drawing. I am known for my art and great stories. I really like the color blue. It is a soothing color and is the color of water and the sky. I go to school at Bethel Springs Elementary School. I am in fourth grade and is in Mrs. Eileen Ferguson’s class. I have a lot of friends  <wbr />there: Madison Wesley, Judith (Judy) Yocum, Mikayla Anderson, Victoria Snyder, Sophia Sands, Celia Tran, and a lot more people! <wbr /> I like the series, Warrior Cats by Erin Hunter. I’m in the orchestra. I play the violin. I like it a lot. Even though it is challenging, it is a fun and great instrument. I often have to be careful in the cafeteria. I am vegan which means that I can’t eat or drink stuff that have milk, eggs, meat, or honey in them. I live in Pennsylvania USA. Feel free to email me; my email:<a href="https://profiles.google.com/?hl=en&amp;tab=mX">tangxinyuan909@gmail.com</a>.</div>\n<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">My other Chinese name is Xinyuan（唐心缘）. But Anne is easier. My favorite sports are tennis, volleyball, soccer, and basketball. My favorite place to go on  <wbr />vacation is Ocean City. I like it’s beach and shops. I like to eat pizza and drink soda. I <wbr /> always look forward to Christmas. You have winter break and you barely learn at school! Then when you get home, you disappear into a pile of gifts! When it is spring break, I go to China. Then stray cats cuddle in my lap. I love the comfort I get from the stroking and purring.</span>\n\n<span style="font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">That is a bit about me!</span>', '[Anne-连载2]心缘在美国成长', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '239-revision', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:47:30', '2013-03-11 06:47:30', '', 239, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=240', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(241, 2, '2013-03-11 06:48:37', '2013-03-11 06:48:37', '<span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">小作者心缘的Note：</span>\r\nAuthor’s Note\r\nDear Reader,\r\nThis is my first book as a young author. I have been inspired by my favorite author Erin Hunter and her famous series, Warriors. When I read the series, I suddenly started loving nature and animals. In this fantasy story, you will find mystery, and power. I hope you enjoy this story about wolves.\r\nAnne Tang （心缘）', '[Anne-连载3]小说连载1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anne-%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd3%e5%b0%8f%e8%af%b4%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd1', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:48:37', '2013-03-11 06:48:37', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=241', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(242, 2, '2013-03-11 06:48:26', '2013-03-11 06:48:26', '小作者心缘的Note：\nAuthor’s Note\nDear Reader,\nThis is my first book as a young author. I have been inspired by my favorite author Erin Hunter and her famous series, Warriors. When I read the series, I suddenly started loving nature and animals. In this fantasy story, you will find mystery, and power. I hope you enjoy this story about wolves.\nAnne Tang （心缘）', '[Anne-连载3]小说连载1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '241-revision', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:48:26', '2013-03-11 06:48:26', '', 241, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=242', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(243, 2, '2013-03-11 06:50:05', '2013-03-11 06:50:05', 'Chapter 1- Claw\r\nThe bright, white stars glittered in the night sky. A cool breeze made a tree’s leaves rustle\r\nas through a leopard paced through the green leaves. The air was silent as the animals\r\nrested after a tiring day.\r\nClaw sniffed a morsel that the No-tails had for left the family of wolves. The No-tails were weird-looking creatures. They had no fur except at the top of their heads. They were different pelts each day. And of course, they had no tails.\r\nClaw wrinkled his nose in disgust and left the morsel. He curled up beneath a birch tree\r\nand placed his fluffy tail over his nose.\r\n“Claw? ” Claw lifted up his head and saw a pale, gray wolf padding toward him.\r\n“Hi, Dove,” Claw greeted his sister.\r\nDove nudged him. ”Come on! Get up!”\r\nClaw heaved himself to his paws. ”Okay, okay. “\r\nHis sister was already padding away. She glanced over her shoulder, the morning sun making her squint. “Let’s see who can race to the other side of the clearing first!”\r\nShe raced away, her paws thumping the sandy ground.\r\nClaw raced after his sister. “That’s not fair!” he complained. “You got a head start!”\r\nDove halted as Claw caught up with her. “You always complain.” Her tail tip twitched.\r\nClaw sniffed. ”You always cheat”, he retorted.\r\n“Are you going to stand there gossiping all day?” The two wolves spun around to see a brown he-wolf. It was Mud, Claw and Dove’s father. “I need you to help me fix some the dens. The wind blew some down yesterday night.” “Okay.” Dove sounded determinedly cheerful. “ Then?” Claw hinted. “Then you may play,” Mud answered.\r\nClaw padded to a cave where the wolves built dens. As he emerged into the cave, he\r\nfound moss, bracken, and heather scattered around the cave.\r\nDove poked her pale head into the cave and then gagged when she saw the scattered,\r\nstale bedding. ”We have to clean up that?” “Yes you do.” A gray she-wolf stepped into the cave. “And I’ll help you.”\r\n“Hi, Mist.” Claw let out a grrrrooo of relief when his mother offered help. Mist started pushing some bedding into a pile. “ Just make eight piles of bedding. It’s that easy. One for me, one for you-“she nodded to Claw, ”-one for you-“she nodded at Dove ,”-one for Mud, another for Lacy, another for Reddy, another for Bear, and one for Kalie.”\r\n“Did somebody say my name?” A russet she-wolf emerged into the cave. “We were just listing everybody’s name because were fixing the nests, Kalie,” Dove told the russet wolf. Kalie’s amber eyes brightened. ”Can I help?”\r\nBy sunhigh, the wolves had finished fixing the nests and were gulping down the new\r\nmorsels. (To be continued next time)', '[Anne-连载4]小说连载2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anne-%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd4%e5%b0%8f%e8%af%b4%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd2', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:50:05', '2013-03-11 06:50:05', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=243', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(244, 2, '2013-03-11 06:49:49', '2013-03-11 06:49:49', 'Chapter 1- Claw\nThe bright, white stars glittered in the night sky. A cool breeze made a tree’s leaves rustle\nas through a leopard paced through the green leaves. The air was silent as the animals\nrested after a tiring day.\nClaw sniffed a morsel that the No-tails had for left the family of wolves. The No-tails were weird-looking creatures. They had no fur except at the top of their heads. They were different pelts each day. And of course, they had no tails.\nClaw wrinkled his nose in disgust and left the morsel. He curled up beneath a birch tree\nand placed his fluffy tail over his nose.\n“Claw? ” Claw lifted up his head and saw a pale, gray wolf padding toward him.\n“Hi, Dove,” Claw greeted his sister.\nDove nudged him. ”Come on! Get up!”\nClaw heaved himself to his paws. ”Okay, okay. “\nHis sister was already padding away. She glanced over her shoulder, the morning sun making her squint. “Let’s see who can race to the other side of the clearing first!”\nShe raced away, her paws thumping the sandy ground.\nClaw raced after his sister. “That’s not fair!” he complained. “You got a head start!”\nDove halted as Claw caught up with her. “You always complain.” Her tail tip twitched.\nClaw sniffed. ”You always cheat”, he retorted.\n“Are you going to stand there gossiping all day?” The two wolves spun around to see a brown he-wolf. It was Mud, Claw and Dove’s father. “I need you to help me fix some the dens. The wind blew some down yesterday night.” “Okay.” Dove sounded determinedly cheerful. “ Then?” Claw hinted. “Then you may play,” Mud answered.\nClaw padded to a cave where the wolves built dens. As he emerged into the cave, he\nfound moss, bracken, and heather scattered around the cave.\nDove poked her pale head into the cave and then gagged when she saw the scattered,\nstale bedding. ”We have to clean up that?” “Yes you do.” A gray she-wolf stepped into the cave. “And I’ll help you.”\n“Hi, Mist.” Claw let out a grrrrooo of relief when his mother offered help. Mist started pushing some bedding into a pile. “ Just make eight piles of bedding. It’s that easy. One for me, one for you-“she nodded to Claw, ”-one for you-“she nodded at Dove ,”-one for Mud, another for Lacy, another for Reddy, another for Bear, and one for Kalie.”\n“Did somebody say my name?” A russet she-wolf emerged into the cave. “We were just listing everybody’s name because were fixing the nests, Kalie,” Dove told the russet wolf. Kalie’s amber eyes brightened. ”Can I help?”\nBy sunhigh, the wolves had finished fixing the nests and were gulping down the new\nmorsels. (To be continued next time)', '[Anne-连载4]小说连载2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '243-revision', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:49:49', '2013-03-11 06:49:49', '', 243, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=244', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(245, 2, '2013-03-11 06:56:52', '2013-03-11 06:56:52', '<span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Chapter1-continue</span>\r\nClaw gulped down his morsel greedily. He liked the taste of it; juicy and tender.\r\n“Hey, Claw, bet you can’t reach one of those red berries!” His sister’s voice was from behind him.\r\nClaw whirled around and glared at Dove. “Bet I can; bet you can’t,” he retorted.\r\nDove’s blue gaze sparkled with mischief. “Prove it then, scaredy pup!”\r\nClaw bristled. His fur bushed up. “Okay,” he spat. “I’ll prove it to you!” He stomped in front of the tree; the one with the berries. The glossy, blood-colored berries were visible through the bright, green leaves. His amber eyes narrowed on the nearest berry. It was about two wolf-lengths up in the tree.\r\nClaw bunched up his muscles and sprang. Thump! Claw had bumped against a branch. He clung on desperately, his claws sinking into the rough bark. “Help!” he yelped. “I can’t hold”-Crack! The branch had broken! No! Help!', '[Anne-连载5]小说连载3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anne-%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd5%e5%b0%8f%e8%af%b4%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd3', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:56:52', '2013-03-11 06:56:52', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=245', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(246, 2, '2013-03-11 06:56:44', '2013-03-11 06:56:44', 'Chapter1-continue\nClaw gulped down his morsel greedily. He liked the taste of it; juicy and tender.\n“Hey, Claw, bet you can’t reach one of those red berries!” His sister’s voice was from behind him.\nClaw whirled around and glared at Dove. “Bet I can; bet you can’t,” he retorted.\nDove’s blue gaze sparkled with mischief. “Prove it then, scaredy pup!”\nClaw bristled. His fur bushed up. “Okay,” he spat. “I’ll prove it to you!” He stomped in front of the tree; the one with the berries. The glossy, blood-colored berries were visible through the bright, green leaves. His amber eyes narrowed on the nearest berry. It was about two wolf-lengths up in the tree.\nClaw bunched up his muscles and sprang. Thump! Claw had bumped against a branch. He clung on desperately, his claws sinking into the rough bark. “Help!” he yelped. “I can’t hold”-Crack! The branch had broken! No! Help!', '[Anne-连载5]小说连载3', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '245-revision', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:56:44', '2013-03-11 06:56:44', '', 245, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=246', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(247, 2, '2013-03-11 06:59:43', '2013-03-11 06:59:43', 'Chapter 2 - Dove\r\nDove watched in dismay as her brother, Claw, scrabbled on the lower branch which he had landed on when the first branch had broke. Her brother’s black-gray fur was bushed up in terror.\r\n“What is going on?” Dove’s mother, Mist’s horrified voice came from beside her.\r\nDove lowered her head. “I and Claw were just playing…”\r\n“Playing?” Mist snapped. “We are wolves, Dove. We are not cats. We. Don’t. Climb.”\r\nDove lowered her head even lower. She had upset her mother and her brother was in trouble.\r\n“What’s happening?” A brown he-wolf stepped up beside Dove.\r\n“I think that’s Claw!” Reddy joined him.” And he’s in trouble!”\r\n“Bear! Reddy! Pointing out useless things is not helping. Why don’t you two do something helpful instead of scaring us even more?” A white she-wolf snapped.\r\nA clang came from behind the wolves. The wolves whirled around. Several peach-colored creatures stood at the end of the clearing pointing and barking to each other. They wore green pelts and had yellow, brown, or black fur on the top of their heads.\r\n“The No-tails will do something,” Mud pointed out. “So there’s no need for us to panic.”\r\n“How can we not panic?” Mist whispered helplessly. “The No-tails-“Crack! Dove looked up as black and gray flashed down from the tree. “No!” she yelped. “Claw is falling!”', '[Anne-连载6]小说连载4', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anne-%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd6%e5%b0%8f%e8%af%b4%e8%bf%9e%e8%bd%bd4', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:59:43', '2013-03-11 06:59:43', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=247', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(248, 2, '2013-03-11 06:59:34', '2013-03-11 06:59:34', 'Chapter 2 - Dove\nDove watched in dismay as her brother, Claw, scrabbled on the lower branch which he had landed on when the first branch had broke. Her brother’s black-gray fur was bushed up in terror.\n“What is going on?” Dove’s mother, Mist’s horrified voice came from beside her.\nDove lowered her head. “I and Claw were just playing…”\n“Playing?” Mist snapped. “We are wolves, Dove. We are not cats. We. Don’t. Climb.”\nDove lowered her head even lower. She had upset her mother and her brother was in trouble.\n“What’s happening?” A brown he-wolf stepped up beside Dove.\n“I think that’s Claw!” Reddy joined him.” And he’s in trouble!”\n“Bear! Reddy! Pointing out useless things is not helping. Why don’t you two do something helpful instead of scaring us even more?” A white she-wolf snapped.\nA clang came from behind the wolves. The wolves whirled around. Several peach-colored creatures stood at the end of the clearing pointing and barking to each other. They wore green pelts and had yellow, brown, or black fur on the top of their heads.\n“The No-tails will do something,” Mud pointed out. “So there’s no need for us to panic.”\n“How can we not panic?” Mist whispered helplessly. “The No-tails-“Crack! Dove looked up as black and gray flashed down from the tree. “No!” she yelped. “Claw is falling!”', '[Anne-连载6]小说连载4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '247-revision', '', '', '2013-03-11 06:59:34', '2013-03-11 06:59:34', '', 247, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=248', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(249, 2, '2013-03-11 07:00:39', '2013-03-11 07:00:39', '星瀚国际中心 唐文谊\r\n2012年年底，首份国际移民报告显示，中国现在已有一定数量的拥有一定财富的精英人士移民海外，有的还正在考虑之中。2011年，中国对世界几个主要的移民国家永久性移民数量超过15万人，其中在美国获得绿卡的人数达6万多人，在中国国际移民总数中排名第一，而作为新兴的EB-5投资移民只有3000多人。\r\n2012年，EB-5投资者已经大大超出以前的数字，因为EB-5的成功率还是挺高的，只要在办理以前投资项目选择好了，成功机率几乎95%以上，当然您需要有真正有经验、懂得项目、诚实的人员和机构为您办理一系列EB-5事项。由于办理EB-5的人数逐渐增多，因而对以前只需不到3年时间就可以获得美国绿卡的EB-5投资移民，目前就会延长一点时间，这很正常，就如生活中当您到任何地方办理事情的时候，如果人少的话，当然不用排队就可直接办理，而当人数多的时候，显然就需排队，所花时间相对就会多一点。\r\nEB-5投资者获得绿卡时间的周期很短，一般在3年左右，而其他大多数移民类至少也需要5年以上的时间、甚至更长。当年我生活工作在美国8年多，最终才获得绿卡。每每想到如今的EB-5绿卡，或者L1绿卡获得人士，正是幸运至极，有雄厚的实力来办理EB-5、L1绿卡，这完全受益于我们祖国的改革开放政策，使我们的国家繁荣昌盛、强大富强，不断地让许多敢于创新、勇于拼搏、勤奋刻苦的各界人士成功再成功，能够有实力去不断地实现自己的人生目标，证明自己的人生价值，并创造了许多新的思想与新的理念，为社会也创造了新的财富，为人们创造了新的就业机会。同时精英们还拥有特殊的国际化的战略眼光展望世界，前瞻性地认识到今后的世界是全球性的、国际化的，在现实生活中他们为走向世界已经迈出了坚实的一大步。\r\n当精英们来到美国后，虽然美国地大物博、环境优美，大多地方都是蓝天、白云、绿草地，但是对于新的精英移民来说，一切还是都要从头开始。从办理社会安全卡、买房、买车、购买各种所需生活用品、孩子学校的选择、医疗保险、交通道路、语言交流的熟悉等等生活中所需的一切，都要自己去一一落实，或许就在这时我们美国的星瀚国际中心的人员可以为您提供方便，为您排除您刚来异国他乡时的不便。\r\n刚来国外时肯定是人生地不熟，就像前一时期，有一位来美国探亲的友人说，美国地方真大，让她自己去买东西，她连出租车都不知到何处去找，更何况居住在美国的乡村别墅，几乎看不到出租车，您走到马路边都需要20分钟左右，就看您房子坐落在何处，大多移民美国人士都在远离城市中心买房，因为美国与国内不同，乡村环境优美，鸟语花香，静如仙境，正是修心养身的绝佳之处，三、五知己围坐在宽大的阳台上，泡一壶好茶，彼此无忧无虑、轻松自在地说天谈地聊东西，让您安静、宁静，心田间始终流荡着一种说不清、道不明的恬静、愉悦，别有洞天，其乐融融，让您会发自内心的真正感受到人生原来是如此美好、美妙。\r\n噢，朋友您很可能会不信，如果是这样，欢迎各位不妨有机会来我家坐一坐、歇一歇，聊一聊尝试一下便知。\r\n\r\n2013年 1月30日 唐文谊写于美国', '开启在美国的新生活', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e5%bc%80%e5%90%af%e5%9c%a8%e7%be%8e%e5%9b%bd%e7%9a%84%e6%96%b0%e7%94%9f%e6%b4%bb', '', '', '2013-03-11 07:00:39', '2013-03-11 07:00:39', '', 0, 'http://liuxue.sh/?p=249', 0, 'post', '', 0),
